ferences of the circular orbit parameters and the fluxes,\nespecially for the $a=-0.9$ case. Instead, in the study of ISCO the negative\nKerr parameter $a=-0.9$ results in less discrepancies in comparison with the\npositive Kerr parameter $a=0.9$.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Mon, 24 Jul 2017 13:21:14 GMT"}],"update_date":"2017-10-02"}
